Tennessee. So I passed the time catching up with several of Josh=E2=80=99s =
partners in the Commanders, including David
Blitzer, Mark Ein, and Mitch Rales, each a legendary investor in his own ri=
ght.

At halftime, my boys and I were ushered into the main owner=E2=80=99s suite=
, where the real action was taking place. I said my hellos to Josh and his =
family; caught a glimpse of Roger Goodell, the NFL commissioner; had a long=
 chat with Adam Silver, the NBA commissioner (and a fellow Duke grad); and =
spied Muriel Bowser, the
mayor of Washington, D.C. Alas, I didn=E2=80=99t see Jay Powell, the chairm=
an of the Federal Reserve, who was there decked out in Commanders merch. I =
